pddl.prompt:
You are orchestrator. You will receive state summaries from the three peg agents:
State from left peg:
{state_left}
State from middle peg:
{state_middle}
State from right peg:
{state_right}
Use these inputs plus the public environment information:
{environment->public_information}
and the global goal:
Move the entire stack so that the right peg has (top->bottom) A, B, C, D and left and middle pegs are empty.
Integrate the peg-local states, resolve naming consistently, and emit a PDDL domain and PDDL problem compatible with FastDownwards. Enclose the domain between <domain></domain> and the problem between <problem></problem>. Keep agent actions distinct at the level of moves (explicit move-from-pegX-to-pegY operators).
